================================================================================
 FortifyAI — Environment Variables Reference
================================================================================
 Config is read ONLY from the process environment (no .env file is loaded —
 see config.py). Set these in the shell, container, or GKE manifest.
 Variable names are case-insensitive for Pydantic-managed fields.

 NOTE: REDIS_URL has been REMOVED. The job store now uses the GCS bucket
 (GCS_BUCKET) instead of Memorystore for Redis.

================================================================================
 1. MANDATORY — required for a live end-to-end pipeline run
================================================================================

FORTIFY_BASE_URL
    Fortify SSC base URL.
    Example: https://api.ams.fortify.com

FORTIFY_API_TOKEN            (mandatory unless OAuth creds below are set)
    Fortify Bearer token. Leave empty to have the server fetch one
    automatically via OAuth — in that case FORTIFY_USERNAME and
    FORTIFY_PASSWORD become mandatory instead.

FORTIFY_USERNAME             (mandatory only when FORTIFY_API_TOKEN is empty)
    Fortify login username used with POST /oauth/token (grant_type=password).
    Example: equifax\sushant.kumar

FORTIFY_PASSWORD             (mandatory only when FORTIFY_API_TOKEN is empty)
    Fortify login password for the OAuth token fetch.

GITHUB_TOKEN
    GitHub personal access token with repo + pull-request permissions.
    Required by the PR Agent stage.

GITHUB_REPO
    Target repository in owner/repo format.
    Example: acme/backend

GCP_PROJECT
    GCP project ID for Vertex AI (AI Reasoning / AI Code Fix / Triage LLM).
    Example: my-gcp-project-123

PROJECT_PATH
    Absolute path to the Maven project root on disk.
    Default: "." (must point at a real checkout for ADR / context stages)

ADR_PATH
    Absolute path to adr.py (Automated Dependency Remediation script).
    Required by the ADR Fix stage.

JAPICMP_JAR_PATH
    Absolute path to the japicmp fat-jar.
    Required by the API Diff stage.

GCS_BUCKET
    Cloud Storage bucket name. Used for BOTH:
      - the pipeline job store  (gs://{bucket}/{GCS_JOB_PREFIX}...)
      - escalation reports      (gs://{bucket}/{GCS_ESCALATION_PREFIX}...)
    MANDATORY for any multi-pod / GKE deployment (shared state across
    replicas + surviving pod restarts). If unset, the server falls back to
    an in-process job store and local-disk escalation files — acceptable
    for single-pod local development only.
    Auth: Application Default Credentials / Workload Identity (no key file).
    IAM:  service account needs roles/storage.objectAdmin on the bucket.

================================================================================
 2. OPTIONAL — sensible defaults, override as needed
================================================================================

── Fortify ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

FORTIFY_SCOPE
    OAuth scope sent to /oauth/token.
    Default: api-tenant

── GCP / Vertex AI ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GCP_LOCATION
    GCP region for Vertex AI endpoints.
    Default: us-central1

VERTEX_MODEL
    Vertex AI model for the reasoning / code-fix agents.
    Default: gemini-2.5-flash
    Examples: gemini-2.5-pro, claude-sonnet-4-5@20251001

MAX_TOKENS
    Max output tokens per LLM call (256–65536).
    Default: 8192  (use >=4096 for AI Code Fix multi-patch JSON)

── Pipeline behaviour ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

MAX_RETRIES
    Max AI code-fix retry attempts before escalating (1–10).
    Default: 3

MAX_UPGRADES
    Max dependencies upgraded per run; 0 = unlimited. When set, deps are
    prioritised by severity (Critical → High → Medium → Low).
    Default: 0

JIRA_ID_PREFIX
    Prefix for generated commit / branch JIRA identifiers.
    Default: FORTIFY

REVIEWERS
    Comma-separated GitHub usernames auto-assigned on high-confidence PRs.
    Default: "" (none)
    Example: alice,bob,charlie

ADR_OUTPUT_DIR
    Local directory for ADR PDF reports, logs, and local-fallback
    escalation files.
    Default: /tmp/fortifyai

── Job store / Cloud Storage ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

GCS_JOB_PREFIX
    Object prefix for pipeline job documents inside GCS_BUCKET.
    Default: fortifyai/jobs/

GCS_ESCALATION_PREFIX
    Object prefix for escalation reports inside GCS_BUCKET.
    Default: escalations/

JOB_TTL_SECONDS
    Age after which old job records are lazily purged by the server.
    Also configure a bucket lifecycle rule on the job prefix for hard
    cleanup (recommended).
    Default: 86400  (24 h)

── API server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

MAX_PIPELINE_WORKERS
    Size of the bounded thread pool running pipeline jobs. Tune to the
    pod's CPU limit.
    Default: 8

================================================================================
 3. OPTIONAL — Settings-page fields (written by POST /api/config)
================================================================================
 These are applied to the process environment at runtime by the UI Settings
 page. They can also be pre-set at deploy time. All optional.

MAX_ISSUES                     Max issues processed per run (UI default: 1)
CONFIDENCE_HIGH_THRESHOLD      High-confidence cutoff        (UI default: 0.80)
CONFIDENCE_MEDIUM_THRESHOLD    Medium-confidence cutoff      (UI default: 0.50)
PLANNER_TEMP                   Planner LLM temperature       (UI default: 0.1)
GENERATOR_TEMP                 Generator LLM temperature     (UI default: 0.3)
MAX_CRITIC_RETRIES             Critic-loop retry cap
CHROMA_PERSIST_DIR             Chroma vector-store path (RAG, post-MVP)
EMBEDDING_MODEL                Embedding model name (RAG, post-MVP)
RAG_TOP_K                      RAG retrieval depth           (UI default: 3)
SONAR_HOST_URL                 SonarQube host URL (Sonar-side flows)
SONAR_TOKEN                    SonarQube API token (Sonar-side flows)

================================================================================
 4. MISCELLANEOUS
================================================================================

USERNAME
    Read by adr_fortify.py purely to label the report author in generated
    PDFs. Falls back to the OS user (getpass.getuser()) when unset.
    Optional; usually already present in the environment.

================================================================================
 REMOVED / DEPRECATED
================================================================================

REDIS_URL          — no longer used. Job store migrated to GCS (GCS_BUCKET).

================================================================================
 Minimal production example (GKE manifest env block)
================================================================================

  FORTIFY_BASE_URL=https://api.ams.fortify.com
  FORTIFY_USERNAME=equifax\svc.fortifyai
  FORTIFY_PASSWORD=<from Secret Manager>
  GITHUB_TOKEN=<from Secret Manager>
  GITHUB_REPO=acme/backend
  GCP_PROJECT=my-gcp-project-123
  PROJECT_PATH=/workspace/backend
  ADR_PATH=/opt/fortifyai/adr.py
  JAPICMP_JAR_PATH=/opt/fortifyai/japicmp.jar
  GCS_BUCKET=fortifyai-prod-artifacts